Reasoning: The paper focuses on the design and feasibility of a technology tool to support social interactions in residential care, specifically through reminiscence-based activities. This topic falls under the domain of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as computer-supported cooperative work (cs.CSCW). The paper also discusses the challenges of designing for both co-located and virtual social interactions, which could be categorized under cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze the collected stories, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
